Document: custom_performance_monitors
Path: godot/tutorials/scripting/debug/custom_performance_monitors.rst
Summary: How to retrieve and display custom performance monitor values in a running Godot project using specific methods and UI elements

Use Performance.get_custom_monitor("category/name") to fetch the value of the custom monitor. You can display the value using a Label, RichTextLabel, custom drawing in 2D, 3D text, or other visualization methods. This method can be used in exported projects as well (debug and release mode), which allows you to create visualizations outside the editor.